deck: Polish omnibus edition of "Expedition. The Gods from Outer Space".
description:
For the first time in a single volume!

Thousands of years ago, Earth was visited by aliens from the planet Des. Led by Ais, the visitors wanted to create an intelligent civilization on our planet. It was not an easy job, considering the fact that the ambitious plans were impeded by mutinies or a mad scientist and his minions. When the situation seemed stable, The Great Brain from Des decided to sink the Great Island where alien scientists were working...

See what happened on Earth, not only according to Däniken!

„Expedition. The Gods from Outer Space” is an epic comic book consisting of 8 issues. Created upon a request from a German publisher between 1970s and 1980s, the story excites with its grand scale, intrigue and visionary drawings by Bogusław Polch.

The comic book has been published in a dozen or so countries, which makes it the most widely know Polish graphic novels!
name: Ekspedycja. Bogowie z kosmosu. Wydanie kolekcjonerskie

description:
Legendary comic book with drawings of Bogusław Polch and script written by Maciej Parowski and Jacek Rodek. For the readers who remember the 1980s it's an opportunity to get back to the reading experience of their youth, and for the younger readers it's a chance to discover one of the most fascinating stories in the Polish comic book history.

Space detective Funky Koval, with the help of his friends and Universs - a private investigation agency - pursues political scandals in which aliens are involved. All this in the company of beautiful women and numerous references to Polish politics.
name: Funky Koval. Wydanie kolekcjonerskie

description:
The heroes are tired. They move forward groping in the darkness of lies and half-truths. Even Funky, cloned through medical droll tricks, turns against himself. He himself, his allies and readers do not know which side is the right side.

Pawns are placed on board. No one is sure of victory.
name: Wbrew sobie

description: After a long break, Boguslaw Polch and Maciej Parowski return to the story of the most famous space detective. Finally, we will see the end of one of the greatest stories in the history of Polish grapgic novels. All masks will drop, hidden alliances will come to light, and humanity and droll will fight in a final showdown. Time speeds up, the old heroes get back to action.
name: Wrogie przejęcie
